06/02/2008
TOKYO, Japan -- Prime Minister Yasuo Fukuda met with visiting Albanian counterpart, Sali Berisha, on Tuesday (February 5th) in Tokyo. 
They discussed ways to boost bilateral ties, with Fukuda assuring Berisha that Japan will support the successful implementation of ongoing reforms. 
He also expressed his country's readiness to help Albania in power supply, education, mining and environmental projects. 
Berisha urged Fukuda to open a Japanese embassy in Tirana as a means of encouraging Japanese investors. 
(Koha Jone, Shekulli - 06/02/08; Prime Minister website - 05/02/08)
